sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client
    participant Bucket as Bucket Service
    participant Meta as Object Metadata Service
    participant Storage as Storage Nodes (K+M)
    participant CDN as CDN / Edge Cache

    Note over Client,Storage: Multipart PUT (large object)
    Client->>Bucket: InitiateMultipartUpload(bucket, key)
    Bucket->>Bucket: Authorize (ACL, policy)
    Bucket-->>Client: upload_id

    loop Each part (5MB - 5GB)
        Client->>Storage: UploadPart(upload_id, part_num, bytes)
        Storage->>Storage: Erasure code 6 data + 3 parity, place across AZs
        Storage-->>Client: ETag(part)
    end

    Client->>Bucket: CompleteMultipartUpload([part_num, etag])
    Bucket->>Meta: Atomic commit: (bucket,key) -> piece locations + version_id
    Meta-->>Bucket: Committed (Raft quorum)
    Bucket-->>Client: 200 OK (etag, version_id)

    Note over Client,CDN: GET with cache
    Client->>CDN: GET /{bucket}/{key}
    alt Cache hit
        CDN-->>Client: Bytes
    else Cache miss
        CDN->>Meta: Lookup (bucket, key)
        Meta-->>CDN: Piece locations + storage_class
        CDN->>Storage: Fetch any K of (K+M) pieces in parallel
        Storage-->>CDN: K pieces
        CDN->>CDN: Reconstruct object via Reed-Solomon
        CDN-->>Client: Bytes (cache populated)
    end

    Note over Storage: Background: scrub checksums, repair under-replicated, GC tombstones
